---
import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
import Footer from '../components/Footer.astro';

const title = "Privacy Policy";
const description = "Antares Systems privacy policy covering data collection, usage, security, and your rights under GDPR and UK Data Protection Act.";
---

<BaseLayout title={title} description={description}>
	<head>
		<meta name="robots" content="noindex" />
	</head>

	<main class="min-h-screen bg-white text-gray-800 font-['Inter']">
		<div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6 py-16 lg:py-24">
			<article class="prose prose-lg max-w-none">
				<h1 class="text-4xl lg:text-5xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8">Privacy Policy</h1>

				<p class="text-gray-600 mb-12">Last updated: {new Date().toLocaleDateString('en-GB', { day: 'numeric', month: 'long', year: 'numeric' })}</p>

				{/* Information we collect */}
				<section class="mb-16">
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">1. Information We Collect</h2>
					<p class="text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
						At Antares Systems, we collect information to provide our IT Asset Disposition (ITAD) services and communicate effectively with our clients. The data we collect falls into the following categories:
					</p>

					<div class="space-y-6">
						<div>
							<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Contact Forms</h3>
							<p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed">When you contact us through our website or service inquiry forms, we collect:</p>
							<ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 pl-4">
								<li>Your full name</li>
								<li>Company name and position</li>
								<li>Professional email address</li>
								<li>Phone number</li>
								<li>Type of IT asset disposition service required</li>
								<li>Any additional information you choose to provide regarding your IT asset disposal needs</li>
							</ul>
						</div>

						<div>
							<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Cookies and Tracking Technologies</h3>
							<p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 leading-relaxed">We use cookies and similar tracking technologies to:</p>
							<ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 pl-4">
								<li>Enhance your experience on our website</li>
								<li>Analyze site usage and traffic patterns</li>
								<li>Maintain website security</li>
								<li>Remember your preferences</li>
							</ul>
							<p class="text-gray-700 mt-4 leading-relaxed">
								The cookies we use are strictly necessary for basic website functionality and do not collect personally identifiable information. You can disable cookies through your browser settings, though this may affect site functionality.
							</p>
						</div>

						<div>
							<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Service Delivery Information</h3>
							<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">In the course of providing our ITAD services, we may collect and process:</p>
							<ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 pl-4 mt-4">
								<li>Asset manifests and inventory lists</li>
								<li>Data destruction certificates</li>
								<li>Compliance documentation</li>
								<li>Service delivery records</li>
								<li>Financial transaction information (processed through secure payment gateways)</li>
							</ul>
						</div>
					</div>
				</section>

				{/* How we use your data */}
				<section class="mb-16">
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">2. How We Use Your Data</h2>
					<p class="text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
						Antares Systems uses your information solely for the purposes of delivering our professional IT asset disposition services and maintaining business relationships. We may use your data to:
					</p>

					<ul class="list-disc list-outside space-y-4 text-gray-700 pl-6">
						<li>
							<strong class="text-gray-900">Provide ITAD services:</strong> Process your inquiries, deliver asset disposition solutions, and manage data destruction according to <a href="/compliance" class="text-blue-600 underline hover:text-blue-800">NIST 800-88 and HMG IS5 standards</a>.
						</li>
						<li>
							<strong class="text-gray-900">Communication:</strong> Respond to your inquiries, provide service updates, and share important compliance information relevant to your asset disposition projects.
						</li>
						<li>
							<strong class="text-gray-900">Service improvement:</strong> Enhance our ITAD processes and maintain the highest standards of data security and environmental responsibility.
						</li>
						<li>
							<strong class="text-gray-900">Compliance documentation:</strong> Maintain records as required by data protection laws, environmental regulations, and industry standards in the UK.
						</li>
						<li>
							<strong class="text-gray-900">Legal obligations:</strong> Fulfill our responsibilities under UK GDPR, Data Protection Act 2018, and other applicable regulations.
						</li>
					</ul>

					<p class="text-gray-700 mt-8 leading-relaxed">
						We will <strong class="text-gray-900">never</strong> sell, rent, or share your personal information with third parties for marketing purposes.
					</p>
				</section>

				{/* Data Security */}
				<section class="mb-16">
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">3. Data Security</h2>
					<p class="text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
						As a specialist in IT asset disposition, Antares Systems maintains the highest standards of data security throughout all business processes. Your information is protected by:
					</p>

					<ul class="list-disc list-outside space-y-4 text-gray-700 pl-6">
						<li>
							<strong class="text-gray-900">Secure data handling protocols:</strong> All personal and business information is processed according to NCSC-approved security standards.
						</li>
						<li>
							<strong class="text-gray-900">Secure data destruction:</strong> Physical assets containing data are destroyed using NIST 800-88 and HMG IS5 compliant methods, including mechanical shredding, degaussing, or secure erasure.
						</li>
						<li>
							<strong class="text-gray-900">Secure storage:</strong> Digital data is stored on encrypted servers with robust access controls and 24/7 security monitoring.
						</li>
						<li>
							<strong class="text-gray-900">Secure transmission:</strong> All data transmitted to or from our website is protected using SSL/TLS 1.2 or higher encryption.
						</li>
						<li>
							<strong class="text-gray-900">Access control:</strong> Your information is only accessible to authorized personnel who require access to perform their duties.
						</li>
						<li>
							<strong class="text-gray-900">Data retention:</strong> We retain your information only for as long as necessary to fulfill our legal and contractual obligations, or as required by relevant regulations in the asset disposition industry.
						</li>
						<li>
							<strong class="text-gray-900">Supplier vetting:</strong> All third-party service providers are thoroughly vetted to ensure they meet our stringent data security and compliance requirements.
						</li>
					</ul>
				</section>

				{/* Compliance with GDPR and UK Data Protection Act */}
				<section class="mb-16">
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">4. Compliance with GDPR and UK Data Protection Act</h2>
					<p class="text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
						Antares Systems is fully committed to complying with all applicable data protection laws, including:
					</p>

					<ul class="list-disc list-outside space-y-4 text-gray-700 pl-6 mb-8">
						<li>The <strong class="text-gray-900">UK General Data Protection Regulation (UK GDPR)</strong></li>
						<li>The <strong class="text-gray-900">Data Protection Act 2018</strong></li>
						<li>The <strong class="text-gray-900">Privacy and Electronic Communications Regulations (PECR)</strong></li>
					</ul>

					<div class="space-y-6">
						<div>
							<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">ICO Registration</h3>
							<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Antares Systems is registered with the Information Commissioner's Office (ICO) under registration number C18880232.</p>
						</div>

						<div>
							<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">Lawful Basis for Processing</h3>
							<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">We process your information based on the following lawful grounds:</p>
							<ul class="list-disc list-inside space-y-2 text-gray-700 pl-4 mt-4">
								<li><strong class="text-gray-900">Contractual necessity:</strong> Processing is necessary for the performance of contracts or taking steps prior to entering into a contract.</li>
								<li><strong class="text-gray-900">Legal obligation:</strong> Processing is necessary for compliance with our legal obligations as an ITAD provider.</li>
								<li><strong class="text-gray-900">Legitimate interests:</strong> Processing is necessary for our legitimate interests in providing IT asset disposition services, subject to appropriate safeguards for your rights.</li>
							</ul>
						</div>

						<div>
							<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-3">International Data Transfers</h3>
							<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">Antares Systems is a London-based company and all data processing activities occur within the UK. We do not routinely transfer personal data outside the United Kingdom. In the event that we must transfer data for specific operational purposes, we ensure appropriate safeguards are in place as required by data protection laws.</p>
						</div>
					</div>
				</section>

				{/* Your rights and Contact information */}
				<section class="mb-16">
					<h2 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6">5. Your Rights and Contact Information</h2>
					<p class="text-gray-700 mb-6 leading-relaxed">
						Under UK data protection laws, you have several important rights concerning your personal information. You may exercise these rights at any time by contacting us using the details provided below.
					</p>

					<ul class="list-disc list-outside space-y-4 text-gray-700 pl-6 mb-8">
						<li>The right to be informed about how your data is collected and used</li>
						<li>The right to access the personal information we hold about you</li>
						<li>The right to request correction of inaccurate or incomplete information</li>
						<li>The right to request erasure of your data in certain circumstances</li>
						<li>The right to restrict processing of your data in certain situations</li>
						<li>The right to data portability for information you have provided</li>
						<li>The right to object to processing based on legitimate interests</li>
						<li>The right to withdraw consent where processing is based on consent</li>
						<li>The right to lodge a complaint with the ICO or another supervisory authority</li>
					</ul>

					<div class="bg-gray-50 rounded-lg p-6">
						<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold text-gray-900 mb-2">Contact Us</h3>
						<p class="text-gray-700 mb-4">
							If you have any questions, concerns, or requests regarding this privacy policy or how we handle your personal information, please contact us:
						</p>

						<address class="not-italic text-gray-700 space-y-2">
							<p>
								<strong class="text-gray-900">Antares Systems</strong><br/>
								London CR2 8PD<br/>
								United Kingdom
							</p>

							<p>
								<strong class="text-gray-900">Email:</strong>
								<a href="mailto:contact@antaressystems.net" class="text-blue-600 hover:text-blue-800">contact@antaressystems.net</a>
							</p>
						</address>
					</div>

					<p class="text-gray-700 mt-8 leading-relaxed">
						We will respond to your request within one calendar month, except in exceptional circumstances where we may need up to two additional months. If we ask you to verify your identity, the response time may be extended by the amount of time it takes to complete that verification.
					</p>
				</section>

				{/* Compliance notice */}
				<section class="border-l-4 border-blue-600 pl-6 py-4 bg-gray-50 rounded-lg">
					<p class="text-gray-700 leading-relaxed">
						<strong class="text-gray-900">Compliance Notice:</strong> This privacy policy has been drafted to comply with NIST 800-88, HMG IS5, UK GDPR, Data Protection Act 2018, and ICO guidelines. All data handling activities adhere to NCSC-approved security standards for secure IT asset disposition.
					</p>
				</section>
			</article>
		</div>
	</main>
	<Footer />
</BaseLayout>
